The paper proposes a meta path planning algorithm that utilizes prior experience to reduce the sample requirement for solving new path planning problems. The algorithm uses a novel neural architecture to learn from experiences and integrate the learned prior with a UCB-type algorithm to achieve an online balance between exploration and exploitation. This work involves machine learning, robotics, and control, which are all relevant to the sub-categories of cs.AI, cs.RO, and cs.SY. Additionally, the paper mentions using neural networks for learning, which is relevant to the sub-category of cs.LG. Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed algorithm on several benchmark problems, which may fall under the sub-category of cs.CV.
